01384 /* Copy to YYRES the contents of YYSTR after stripping away unnecessary

01393 {

01395     {
01396       YYSIZE_T yyn = 0;
01397       char const *yyp = yystr;
01398 
01399       for (;;)
01400         switch (*++yyp)
01401           {

01403           case ',':

01460       YY_("syntax error, unexpected %s, expecting %s");

01463       YY_("syntax error, unexpected %s, expecting %s or %s or %s or %s");
01464 # endif

01471                     + sizeof yyexpecting - 1

01602 /*----------.
01603 | yyparse.  |
01604 `----------*/
01605 
01606 #ifdef YYPARSE_PARAM
01607 #if (defined __STDC__ || defined __C99__FUNC__ \
01608      || defined __cplusplus || defined _MSC_VER)
01609 int
01610 yyparse (void *YYPARSE_PARAM)

01613 yyparse (YYPARSE_PARAM)
01614     void *YYPARSE_PARAM;
01615 #endif
01616 #else /* ! YYPARSE_PARAM */
01617 #if (defined __STDC__ || defined __C99__FUNC__ \
01618      || defined __cplusplus || defined _MSC_VER)
01619 int
01620 yyparse (void)
01621 #else
01622 int
01623 yyparse ()
01624 
01625 #endif
01626 #endif
01627 {
01628   
01629   int yystate;
01630   int yyn;
01631   int yyresult;
01632   /* Number of tokens to shift before error messages enabled.  */
01633   int yyerrstatus;
01634   /* Look-ahead token as an internal (translated) token number.  */
01635   int yytoken = 0;
01636 #if YYERROR_VERBOSE
01637   /* Buffer for error messages, and its allocated size.  */
01638   char yymsgbuf[128];
01639   char *yymsg = yymsgbuf;
01640   YYSIZE_T yymsg_alloc = sizeof yymsgbuf;
01641 #endif
01642 
01643   /* Three stacks and their tools:
01644      `yyss': related to states,
01645      `yyvs': related to semantic values,
01646      `yyls': related to locations.
01647 
01648      Refer to the stacks thru separate pointers, to allow yyoverflow
01649      to reallocate them elsewhere.  */
01650 
01651   /* The state stack.  */
01652   yytype_int16 yyssa[YYINITDEPTH];
01653   yytype_int16 *yyss = yyssa;
01654   yytype_int16 *yyssp;
01655 
01656   /* The semantic value stack.  */
01657   YYSTYPE yyvsa[YYINITDEPTH];
01658   YYSTYPE *yyvs = yyvsa;
01659   YYSTYPE *yyvsp;
01660 
01661 
01662 
01663 #define YYPOPSTACK(N)   (yyvsp -= (N), yyssp -= (N))
01664 
01665   YYSIZE_T yystacksize = YYINITDEPTH;
01666 
01667   /* The variables used to return semantic value and location from the
01668      action routines.  */
01669   YYSTYPE yyval;
01670 
01671 
01672   /* The number of symbols on the RHS of the reduced rule.
01673      Keep to zero when no symbol should be popped.  */
01674   int yylen = 0;
01675 
01676   YYDPRINTF ((stderr, "Starting parse\n"));
01677 
01678   yystate = 0;
01679   yyerrstatus = 0;
01680   yynerrs = 0;
01681   yychar = YYEMPTY;             /* Cause a token to be read.  */
01682 
01683   /* Initialize stack pointers.
01684      Waste one element of value and location stack
01685      so that they stay on the same level as the state stack.
01686      The wasted elements are never initialized.  */
01687 
01688   yyssp = yyss;
01689   yyvsp = yyvs;
01690 
01691   goto yysetstate;
01692 
01693 /*------------------------------------------------------------.
01694 | yynewstate -- Push a new state, which is found in yystate.  |
01695 `------------------------------------------------------------*/
01696  yynewstate:
01697   /* In all cases, when you get here, the value and location stacks
01698      have just been pushed.  So pushing a state here evens the stacks.  */
01699   yyssp++;
01700 
01701  yysetstate:
01702   *yyssp = yystate;
01703 
01704   if (yyss + yystacksize - 1 <= yyssp)
01705     {
01706       /* Get the current used size of the three stacks, in elements.  */
01707       YYSIZE_T yysize = yyssp - yyss + 1;
01708 
01709 #ifdef yyoverflow
01710       {
01711         /* Give user a chance to reallocate the stack.  Use copies of
01712            these so that the &'s don't force the real ones into
01713            memory.  */
01714         YYSTYPE *yyvs1 = yyvs;
01715         yytype_int16 *yyss1 = yyss;
01716 
01717 
01718         /* Each stack pointer address is followed by the size of the
01719            data in use in that stack, in bytes.  This used to be a
01720            conditional around just the two extra args, but that might
01721            be undefined if yyoverflow is a macro.  */
01722         yyoverflow (YY_("memory exhausted"),
01723                     &yyss1, yysize * sizeof (*yyssp),
01724                     &yyvs1, yysize * sizeof (*yyvsp),
01725 
01726                     &yystacksize);
01727 
01728         yyss = yyss1;
01729         yyvs = yyvs1;
01730       }
01731 #else /* no yyoverflow */
01732 # ifndef YYSTACK_RELOCATE
01733       goto yyexhaustedlab;
01734 # else
01735       /* Extend the stack our own way.  */
01736       if (YYMAXDEPTH <= yystacksize)
01737         goto yyexhaustedlab;
01738       yystacksize *= 2;
01739       if (YYMAXDEPTH < yystacksize)
01740         yystacksize = YYMAXDEPTH;
01741 
01742       {
01743         yytype_int16 *yyss1 = yyss;
01744         union yyalloc *yyptr =
01745           (union yyalloc *) YYSTACK_ALLOC (YYSTACK_BYTES (yystacksize));
01746         if (! yyptr)
01747           goto yyexhaustedlab;
01748         YYSTACK_RELOCATE (yyss);
01749         YYSTACK_RELOCATE (yyvs);
01750 
01751 #  undef YYSTACK_RELOCATE
01752         if (yyss1 != yyssa)
01753           YYSTACK_FREE (yyss1);
01754       }
01755 # endif
01756 #endif /* no yyoverflow */
01757 
01758       yyssp = yyss + yysize - 1;
01759       yyvsp = yyvs + yysize - 1;
01760 
01761 
01762       YYDPRINTF ((stderr, "Stack size increased to %lu\n",
01763                   (unsigned long int) yystacksize));
01764 
01765       if (yyss + yystacksize - 1 <= yyssp)
01766         YYABORT;
01767     }
01768 
01769   YYDPRINTF ((stderr, "Entering state %d\n", yystate));
01770 
01771   goto yybackup;
01772 
01773 /*-----------.
01774 | yybackup.  |
01775 `-----------*/
01776 yybackup:
01777 
01778   /* Do appropriate processing given the current state.  Read a
01779      look-ahead token if we need one and don't already have one.  */
01780 
01781   /* First try to decide what to do without reference to look-ahead token.  */
01782   yyn = yypact[yystate];
01783   if (yyn == YYPACT_NINF)
01784     goto yydefault;
01785 
01786   /* Not known => get a look-ahead token if don't already have one.  */
01787 
01788   /* YYCHAR is either YYEMPTY or YYEOF or a valid look-ahead symbol.  */
01789   if (yychar == YYEMPTY)
01790     {
01791       YYDPRINTF ((stderr, "Reading a token: "));
01792       yychar = YYLEX;
01793     }
01794 
01795   if (yychar <= YYEOF)
01796     {
01797       yychar = yytoken = YYEOF;
01798       YYDPRINTF ((stderr, "Now at end of input.\n"));
01799     }
01800   else
01801     {
01802       yytoken = YYTRANSLATE (yychar);
01803       YY_SYMBOL_PRINT ("Next token is", yytoken, &yylval, &yylloc);
01804     }
01805 
01806   /* If the proper action on seeing token YYTOKEN is to reduce or to
